br.labsec.thesis.polynomials

Class Polynomial

  • java.lang.Object
    • br.labsec.thesis.polynomials.Polynomial
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Polynomial>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Trinomial

    public class Polynomial
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Polynomial>
    An immutable polynomial in the finite field GF(2^k) Supports standard arithmetic in the field, as well as reducibility tests.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  Polynomial.Reducibility
      An enumeration representing the reducibility of the polynomial A polynomial p(x) in GF(2^k) is called irreducible over GF[2^k] if it is non-constant and cannot be represented as the product of two or more non-constant polynomials from GF(2^k).
